      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, and finely dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-5-1647969987174-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-5-1647969987174-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-5-1647969987174-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-5-1647969987174-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-5-1647969987174-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> and <strong>carrot</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4 min or until softened</p><p>Boil a kettle, then peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-5-1647969991856-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-5-1647969991856-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-5-1647969991856-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-5-1647969991856-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-5-1647969991856-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion and carrot have softened, add your <strong>meat-free mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) to the pan and increase the heat to high</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Add 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>to a pot over a low heat with your <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong> and leave to infuse for 4-5 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-5-1647969997912-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-5-1647969997912-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-5-1647969997912-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-5-1647969997912-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-5-1647969997912-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong> in 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[455ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[650ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>baby leaf salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1647970005836-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1647970005836-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1647970005836-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1647970005836-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1647970005836-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the meat-free mince has browned, tear your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> into the pan with your hands</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 5-7 min or until thickened to a ragù-like consistency – this is your <strong>meat-free ragù</strong></p><p>Remove the <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong> from the infused milk and discard</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-5-1647970023858-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-5-1647970023858-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-5-1647970023858-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-5-1647970023858-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-5-1647970023858-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> to a separate pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span><strong> flour </strong>and stir with a wooden spoon for 1 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>infused</strong> <strong>milk</strong> gradually and whisk for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Remove from the heat and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>béchamel</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-5-1647970029461-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-5-1647970029461-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-5-1647970029461-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-5-1647970029461-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-5-1647970029461-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Layer some of the <strong>ragù </strong>over the bottom of an<strong> oven-proof dish</strong>, then top with some of your <strong>lasagne sheets</strong></p><p>Repeat this process until you end up with a final layer of lasagne sheets</p><p>Tip: You may need to layer differently depending on the size of your dish</p><p>Cover with the <strong>béchamel</strong>, top with the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and cook in the oven for 30 min or until the pasta is cooked</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>– this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>meat-free mince lasagne</strong> with the <strong>baby leaf salad</strong> to the side and the <strong>dressing</strong> drizzled over and enjoy!</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Loved this recipe? Us too! That’s why it’s one of our Everyday Favourites, available every week.</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 8,
